## 1. Milestone Popup Fix ✅

The popup no longer auto-hides. Add a close button:

1. In your **MilestonePopup** panel, add a **Button** child → name it `MilestoneCloseBtn`
2. Style: "✕" or "OK" text
3. In HUDManager Inspector, assign `MilestoneCloseBtn` to the `Milestone Close Button` field

---

## 2. Create Manager GameObjects

In your **game scene**, create an empty GameObject called `Systems` and add these components:

```
📁 Systems (existing or new)
├── 📜 PawCoinManager
├── 📜 DailyTaskManager
├── 📜 AchievementManager
├── 📜 MiniGameManager
└── 📜 RoomManager
```

Then in **GameManager** Inspector, assign the new references:

| Field | Drag From |
|---|---|
| Paw Coin Manager | Systems → PawCoinManager |
| Daily Task Manager | Systems → DailyTaskManager |
| Achievement Manager | Systems → AchievementManager |
| Room Manager | Systems → RoomManager |

---

## 3. RoomManager Setup

Select the **RoomManager** component and configure:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Background Renderer | Your background SpriteRenderer |
| Cat AI | Cat → CatAI component |
| Rooms[0].roomId | `living_room` |
| Rooms[0].roomName | `Living Room` |
| Rooms[0].unlockCost | `0` |
| Rooms[0].unlockedByDefault | ✅ |
| Rooms[0].backgroundSprite | Your living room sprite |
| Rooms[0].wanderBoundsMin | `(-7, -3)` |
| Rooms[0].wanderBoundsMax | `(7, -1)` |
| Rooms[1].roomId | `kitchen` |
| Rooms[1].roomName | `Kitchen` |
| Rooms[1].unlockCost | `500` |
| Rooms[1].backgroundSprite | Your kitchen sprite |
| Rooms[2].roomId | `bedroom` |
| Rooms[2].roomName | `Bedroom` |
| Rooms[2].unlockCost | `800` |
| Rooms[2].backgroundSprite | Your bedroom sprite |

---

## 4. Room Switcher UI

In your Canvas, add navigation buttons:

```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 RoomSwitcherUI (script)
    ├── 🔘 LeftArrowBtn ← "◀"
    ├── 📝 RoomNameText
    └── 🔘 RightArrowBtn → "▶"
```

Position at the **top-center** of the screen. Assign references in Inspector.

---

## 5. Shop System Setup

### Create the Shop Panel

```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 ShopPanel (hidden by default)
    ├── 📜 ShopUI (script)
    ├── 📝 CoinDisplay — "0 🐾"
    ├── 🔘 TabRooms — "Rooms"
    ├── 🔘 TabFurniture — "Furniture"
    ├── 📁 ScrollView
    │   └── 📁 Content (Vertical Layout Group + Content Size Fitter)
    ├── 🔘 CloseButton — "✕"
    └── 📁 ConfirmDialog (hidden by default)
        ├── 📝 ConfirmText
        ├── 🔘 ConfirmBuy — "Buy"
        └── 🔘 ConfirmCancel — "Cancel"
```

### Create the Item Slot Prefab

1. Create a UI element (Panel or Button) with:
   - `Image` (icon), `TMP_Text` (name), `TMP_Text` (cost), `Button`, optional `CanvasGroup`
   - A child "OwnedBadge" Image (✓ checkmark, hidden by default)
2. Add the `ShopItemSlotUI` script
3. Assign references, save as **Prefab** in `Assets/Prefabs/UI/`

### Configure Shop Catalog

In `ShopUI` Inspector, set the **Catalog** array with all items:

| # | itemId | itemName | Cost | Category | catInteraction | targetRoomId |
|---|--------|----------|------|----------|----------------|---|
| 0 | `living_room` | Living Room | 0 | Room | None | — |
| 1 | `kitchen` | Kitchen | 500 | Room | None | — |
| 2 | `bedroom` | Bedroom | 800 | Room | None | — |
| 3 | `cat_bed` | Cozy Cat Bed | 100 | Furniture | SleepOn | living_room |
| 4 | `scratch_post` | Scratching Post | 80 | Furniture | Scratch | living_room |
| 5 | `cardboard_box` | Cardboard Box | 50 | Furniture | HideIn | living_room |
| 6 | `plush_cushion` | Plush Cushion | 120 | Furniture | SitOn | living_room |
| 7 | `cat_tower` | Cat Tower | 250 | Furniture | PlayWith | living_room |
| 8 | `kitchen_rug` | Kitchen Rug | 60 | Furniture | SitOn | kitchen |
| 9 | `window_shelf` | Sunny Window Shelf | 150 | Furniture | SleepOn | kitchen |
| 10 | `herb_plant` | Herb Plant | 70 | Furniture | Scratch | kitchen |
| 11 | `fish_tank` | Fish Tank | 200 | Furniture | PlayWith | kitchen |
| 12 | `fluffy_pillow` | Fluffy Pillow | 90 | Furniture | SleepOn | bedroom |
| 13 | `yarn_basket` | Yarn Basket | 100 | Furniture | PlayWith | bedroom |
| 14 | `bookshelf_perch` | Bookshelf Perch | 180 | Furniture | SitOn | bedroom |

For each item, assign an **Icon** sprite and an **Item Sprite** (the actual furniture graphic).

### Add a Shop Button to HUD

Add a button on your HUD that calls `ShopUI.Open()`:
```csharp
[SerializeField] private ShopUI shopUI;
[SerializeField] private Button shopButton;

void Start() {
    shopButton.onClick.AddListener(() => shopUI.Open());
}
```

