## 8. Furniture Placement

### Create Furniture Prefab

1. Create an empty GameObject → name `FurniturePrefab`
2. Add: `SpriteRenderer`, `BoxCollider2D`, `FurnitureInstance`
3. Save as Prefab in `Assets/Prefabs/`

### Placement UI
```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 FurniturePlacementPanel (hidden by default)
    ├── 📜 FurniturePlacementUI (script)
    ├── 📁 InventoryScrollView → Content
    ├── 🔘 ConfirmButton (hidden initially)
    ├── 🔘 CancelButton (hidden initially)
    ├── 🔘 RemoveButton
    └── 🔘 CloseButton
```

Assign:
- **Furniture Prefab**: your created prefab
- **Shop UI**: reference to ShopUI (for looking up item data)
- **Inventory Slot Prefab**: a simple Button+Text prefab

Add a "🪑 Decorate" HUD button that calls `FurniturePlacementUI.Open()`.

---

## 9. Cat Fishing Mini-Game

### Create Fish Prefab

1. Create an empty GameObject → name `FishPrefab`
2. Add: `SpriteRenderer` (fish sprite), `CircleCollider2D` (radius ~0.4), `Fish`
3. Save as Prefab

### Mini-Game UI Setup
```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 MiniGamePanel (hidden by default, full-screen)
    ├── 📜 CatFishingGame (script)
    ├── 📝 ScoreText — "0"
    ├── 📝 TimerText — "30s"
    ├── 📝 InstructionText — "Tap fish to catch them!"
    ├── 🔘 StartButton — "Start!"
    ├── 🔘 CloseButton — "✕"
    ├── 🖼️ CatPaw (optional, hidden by default)
    └── 📁 GameOverPanel (hidden by default)
        ├── 📝 FinalScoreText — "Score: 0"
        ├── 📝 CoinsEarnedText — "+0 🐾"
        ├── 🔘 PlayAgainButton — "Play Again"
        └── 🔘 ExitButton — "Exit"
```

### FishSpawner Setup

1. Add `FishSpawner` component to the same object as `CatFishingGame` (or a child)
2. Configure:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Fish Prefab | FishPrefab |
| Base Spawn Interval | 1.5 |
| Min Spawn Interval | 0.4 |
| Golden Chance | 0.1 |
| Base Speed | 2 |
| Max Speed | 5 |

3. In `CatFishingGame`, assign `FishSpawner` and `MiniGameManager` references

### Opening the Mini-Game

Add a "🐟 Fish" HUD button that calls `CatFishingGame.Open()`.

---

## 10. HUD Buttons Summary

Add these buttons to your existing HUD Canvas:

| Button | Action | Position |
|---|---|---|
| 🛒 Shop | `ShopUI.Open()` | Bottom bar |
| 📋 Tasks | `DailyTaskUI.Open()` | Bottom bar |
| 🏆 Achievements | `AchievementUI.OpenList()` | Bottom bar |
| 🪑 Decorate | `FurniturePlacementUI.Open()` | Bottom bar |
| 🐟 Fish | `CatFishingGame.Open()` | Bottom bar |
| 🐾 Coins | Display only | Top bar |

### Paw Coin Display on HUD

Add a TMP_Text to your HUD and subscribe to coin changes:

```csharp
[SerializeField] private TextMeshProUGUI coinText;

void Start() {
    if (PawCoinManager.Instance != null)
        PawCoinManager.Instance.OnCoinsChanged += (c) => coinText.text = $"{c} 🐾";
}
```

---

## 11. Testing Tips

> [!TIP]
> **Quick test coins**: In Unity Play Mode, use the Console to add coins:
> `PawCoinManager.Instance.AddCoins(1000, "debug");`

> [!TIP]
> **Reset save data**: Call `SaveSystem.DeleteSave()` from any script or the Console to test fresh start flows.

> [!WARNING]
> **Build Settings**: If you have a MenuScene, both `MenuScene` and `SampleScene` must be in **File → Build Settings** for `SceneManager.LoadScene` to work.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Existing save data**: Since GameData has new fields with defaults, existing saves will load fine — new `List<>` fields deserialize as empty lists, coins default to 0.
